<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc32bde46-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s1985"><num value="1985">§ 1985.</num><heading> Decisions by the Secretary</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Except in the event of suit as provided in <ref href="/us/usc/t38/s1984">section 1984 of this title</ref>, or other appropriate court proceedings, all decisions rendered by the Secretary under the provisions of this chapter shall be final and conclusive on all questions of law or fact, and no other official of the United States shall have jurisdiction to review any such decisions.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc32bde47-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(<ref href="/us/pl/85/857">Pub. L. 85–857</ref>, <date date="1958-09-02">Sept. 2, 1958</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/72/1167">72 Stat. 1167</ref>, § 785; renumbered § 1985 and amended <ref href="/us/pl/102/83">Pub. L. 102–83</ref>, §§ 4(b)(1), (2)(E), 5(a), (c)(1), <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/404-406">105 Stat. 404–406</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc32bde48-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">
